@Darthparralax: shut up. This and [Griselbrand](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Griselbrand) fill up very different niches, you know? You're comparing apples to oranges here.  
Even in Kaalia or reanimator, Gris isn't strictly better than this. If for some reason you fail to cheat it into play, try getting 8 mana (4 of it color-specific) with the amount of accel and fixing Kaalia decks usually run. I dare you.  

That said, I love this card to death. Both artwork and mechanics. Wizards seem to be hellbent on printing powerful black spells attached to demons lately, don't they? This and [Phyrexian Arena](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phyrexian Arena), [Reaper from the Abyss](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reaper from the Abyss) and [The Abyss](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=The Abyss), [Griselbrand](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Griselbrand) and [Necropotence](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Necropotence), [Rune-scarred Demon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rune-scarred Demon) and [Demonic Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demonic Tutor)...

